-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Carl Zeiss Meditec, Interserve 
-- 
-- Mon Jun 30, 2014 01:30AM EDT
-- None



June 30 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including Carl Zeiss Meditec and Interserve, on Monday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Carl Zeiss Meditec AG <AFXG.DE>: Berenberg raises to buy from hold * Interserve <IRV.L>: Numis raises to buy from addFollowing is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Monday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.  * Aberdeen Asset Management <ADN.L>: Barclays raises target to 510p from 490p; overweight * British American Tobacco <BATS.L>: Jefferies raises price target to 3900p; rating buy * Cairn Energy <CNE.L>: Jefferies cuts price target to 285p from 385p; rating buy  * Carl Zeiss Meditec AG <AFXG.DE>: Berenberg raises to buy from hold * Carl Zeiss Meditec AG <AFXG.DE>: Berenberg raises target to 27 euros from 25 euros  * Fresenius Medical Care <FMEG.DE>: Jefferies cuts to underperform; price target to 43 euros * Fresenius SE <FREG.DE>: Jefferies raises target to 126 euros from 113 euros;rating buy * Imperial Tobacco <IMT.L>: Jefferies raises price target to 2700p; rating hold  * Interserve <IRV.L>: Numis raises to buy from add * Intesa Sanpaolo <ISP.MI>: SocGen adds to Premium List; rating buy * Moscow Exchange <MOEX.MM>: Renaissance Capital raises target to 85 roubles from 75 roubles * PKN Orlen <PKN.WA>: SocGen raises to hold from sell rating * Syngenta <SYNN.VX>: JP Morgan cuts to underweight from neutral * Syngenta <SYNN.VX>: JP Morgan cuts target to Sfr 250 from Sfr 340